.TH "wait_for_completion_killable" 9 "wait_for_completion_killable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
wait_for_completion_killable \- - waits for completion of a task (killable)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" wait_for_completion_killable
.BI "(struct completion *x "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "x" 12
holds the state of this particular completion
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This waits to be signaled for completion of a specific task. It can be
interrupted by a kill signal.
.SH "RETURN"
-ERESTARTSYS if interrupted, 0 if completed.
